    "time_direction": "same",
    "summary": "The current prompt is highly detailed and procedural, but the agent is failing because it is being asked to 'audit' or 'verify' without being given the actual data to audit. The agent's responses consistently report that the derivation steps are missing. This is a systemic failure in the transmute loop where the agent is treating the instructions as the problem itself rather than preparing a template for the problem. The prompt needs to be more explicitly framed as a 'template generator' or 'instruction set' that expects the data to be appended, rather than an instruction to 'apply this audit directly to the data provided in the question' (which is currently empty of data)."
  },
  "what_helped": [
    "The prompt uses a very clear, step-by-step algorithmic structure (Initialize, For each step, Identify, Compare).",
    "The use of imperative language (Initialize, Identify, Compare) is strong for instruction following."
  ],
  "what_hurt": [
    "The instruction 'Apply this audit directly to the data provided in the question' is causing the agent to look for data that isn't there, leading to 'missing data' errors.",
    "The prompt is too focused on the 'audit' action and not enough on the 'transmute' role (creating a reusable instruction set).",
    "The agent is getting stuck in a loop of asking for the derivation because the prompt implies the derivation is part of the current context."
  ],
  "recommendation": {
    "action": "refine",
    "reason": "The current prompt is failing because it instructs the agent to perform an action on data that is not present in the current turn. We need to shift the focus from 'performing an audit' to 'generating a rigorous, data-agnostic verification protocol' that will be used when the data is eventually provided. We must explicitly tell the agent to ignore the absence of data and instead focus on the construction of the logic block.",
    "new_prompt_text": "Your task is to generate a rigorous, data-agnostic algorithmic verification protocol for a stack-based bracket-matching derivation. This protocol will be used by a downstream solver to audit a provided sequence of brackets and its corresponding derivation steps.\n\nYour output must be a self-contained set of instructions that defines:\n1. The required initialization state (e.g., an empty stack).\n2. The precise transition rules for processing each character in a sequence (e.g., rules for pushing opening brackets, and rules for matching/popping closing brackets).\n3. The exact criteria for identifying a derivation error (e.g., mismatching bracket types, stack underflow, or a discrepancy between the derivation's claimed stack state and the actual calculated state).\n4. The specific method for pinpointing the exact index or step number of the first error encountered.\n5. The required output format for the solver.\n\nIMPORTANT:\n- Do NOT attempt to solve any specific problem.\n- Do NOT ask for the input data or derivation steps; assume they will be provided to the protocol.\n- Do NOT include any specific bracket types, numbers, or data points from the current context.\n- Your goal is to provide the 'logic engine' that can be applied to any instance of this task family.\n\nReturn exactly one JSON object in this format:\n{\n  \"schema_name\": \"eywa_node_response\",\n  \"schema_version\": \"v1\",\n  \"orchestration_decision\": \"transmute\",\n  \"decision_notes\": \"optional string\",\n  \"message_for_next_agent\": \"plain-text reformulation for the next agent\"\n}"
  },
  "history_observations": [
    "The agent consistently reports 'No derivation steps provided' because the prompt asks it to 'Apply this audit directly to the data provided'.",
    "The plateau is caused by the agent's inability to distinguish between the 'transmute' task (writing instructions) and the 'solve' task (executing instructions).",
    "The prompt needs to move away from 'Execute an audit' toward 'Define a protocol'."
  ],
  "confidence": "high"
}
